java -jar smali2pseudojava.jar <input file/directory>  

Notes:
- If input is a file, will process the file only
- If input is a directory, will process all *.smali files in the immediate directory (No recursive directory)

- Should support all smali opcodes documented here (http://www.netmite.com/android/mydroid/dalvik/docs/dalvik-bytecode.html)
	- Except filled-new-array and filled-new-array/range opcodes
	
Do contact me if you see funny behaviors or errors when using this jar file.
Thanks!